node.text:
Protein icecream FTW

150g frozen banana
150ml almond milk (unsweetened)
25g @foodspring_athletics 3K chocolate protein
Sweetener to taste (vanilla)
Optional - peanut butter / peanut butter powder. 

Mix all ingredients and put in freezer - stir frequently to avoid crystallization. 

My favorite snack!

node.text:
August ‘19, ‘20 and ‘21. 

You’ve ever wondered what the most important thing you can do for you body is? Well I’ll let you in on a small secret - it’s PROPER food. @rpstrength makes this as easy as it possibly can be. Eating is all about balance and not even the best of us can keep a straight line every day. The @rpstrength app simplifies it and it’s possible to adjust based on your current needs to hit your goals - whether it’s making the CrossFit Games, growing a baby or something like else 

I never starved myself , I never went on a “diet” I eat well and I eat enough 

Use code RPSTRENGTH for a discounted subscription for 6 months.

#dottir #diet #lean #balance #rpstrength #fitness #food

node.text:
One week has passed since one of the most memorable moments of my athletic career. 

Lifting in front of a crowd is always an incredible feeling, but this night was special. 

This 200lbs snatch is a few pounds below my lifetime best, but will always stand out as my BIGGEST LIFT in competition. 

It was the moment where I started to believe that I COULD do this. Not just BE at the CrossFit Games, but COMPETE. 

Whether you’re an athlete or not, these are the moments we should all work hard to achieve. The moment where you allow yourself to fully commit, make yourself vulnerable and take the leap. This is where we truly live. 

#dottir #snatch #believe #commitment #nohesitation #taketheleap #makethepull #crossfit #fitness #motivation #faith 🎥: @prestonsmithphotography

node.text:
What most people see, is just the tip of the iceberg. 

No one can walk this walk alone. And honestly, I’m not even sure it would be worth it even if you could. 

It all starts with family, family by blood or by choice. Your select few that you allow close, those select few who knows you better than you know yourself. Those select few who will support you no matter what. 

This past weekend was the culmination of years of hard work and a 12 month stretch that tested me and my TEAM more than any season before. 

If I had not had a great support system in 2009 I would have never travelled to Aromas and I would have never found my sport. If I hadn’t had people push me to be the best me in 2010 I would have never stood on the podium. I would never have become the fittest on earth, never met @frederikaegidius and never stood in front of the amazing crowds who cheer us through the CrossFit Games every year. 

This year was special. 

▶️ My coach @jamitikkanen had to constantly monitor and alter my training to make sure I wouldn’t strain my body more than it could handle.
▶️my physical therapist @andrewmartindc who made it out to Iceland 3!! times during this pandemic to get my fragile body back on track along with remote video treatment
▶️my training partners - all of you who kept my head in the game, even when I didn’t feel like I could compete. 
▶️my sports psychologist who always knew the right thing to say without telling me what to do
▶️my manager @loudlivesports who made sure I had as few distractions from training and competing as possible
▶️ @katrintanja - Katrin, I love you. Always by my side even when you’re not. 
▶️ My sponsors, who many have been by my side for Years now, never pressure and give me the support to do what I LOVE. @reebok @roguefitness @transparentlabs @drinkyerbae @sidekicktool @rpstrength @nuunhydration 

Now, I will spend time with my daughter, my parents, my boyfriend and brothers - 2021 has been a magical year. Thank you. 

#crossfit #grateful

node.text:
I can’t put this feeling into words so I think I’ll spend the next few days digesting what has just happened. 

This one is for you Grandma, for Freyja, for Frederik, for Jami, for my parents. For everyone who believed on me, even when I didn’t. 

For now I just want to say thank you. To everyone who has shown me support. To everyone that kept believing in me. To everyone that helped me in my recovery from birth. 
All the messages on social media it’s not just noise. Those messages fuels me and motives me to keep working hard, also on days I don’t want to. Motivation can come from many different places. Motivation is not always there but if you’re not looking you’ll never find it.

#enjoythejourney #dottir #motivation #inspiration #comeback 📸 @flashlight.fitness

node.text:
UNLOCK YOUR CAN-DO ATTITUDE!

I am STOKED to announce that I am partnering with @drinkyerbae!!

 Have you ever sat down and talked with a stranger and within moments felt like you’ve know each other for years?? 

That’s exactly how I felt when I met the founders of this incredible company. 

There’s a lot of caffeinated drinks out there,  maybe you should try reading on them and see what you are actually drinking. 

When I choose partners to work with I always ask myself this: “would I recommend this to my parents..?” If I can’t wholeheartedly say YES, then I will not put my name behind it. 

@drinkyerbae however, is a BIG YES. They are new to this space but I’m sure that they will fit perfectly with this community that have been my life for the last 13 years! 

I’m so proud to represent this company and what it stands for! 

#yerbae #yerbaemate #naturalcaffeine #unlockyourcandoattitude #partner #dottir #energy #cleandrink
